==Old English==
===Etymology===
Common Germanic, from Indo-European ''*leb-, *lob-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[slepa]], Old High German ''slāfan'' (German [[schlafen]]), Old Saxon ''slāpan'' (Dutch [[slapen]]), Gothic [[𐍃𐌻𐌴𐍀𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'slæ:pan/

===Verb===
'''slǣpan''' (class VII strong: '''slǣpþ''' ‘he sleeps’; '''slēp''' ‘he slept’; '''slēpon''' ‘they slept’; '''ġeslǣpen''' past participle)
# to [[sleep]]

